reater}P. speciosa{\textless}/italic{\textgreater}, which exhibited high specificity for {\textless}italic{\textgreater}Symbiodinium{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} C3 like across the depth gradient, was indicative of greater amounts of storage lipids contained in the deep colonies.{\textless}/p{\textgreater} {\textless}/sec{\textgreater} {\textless}sec{\textgreater} {\textless}title{\textgreater}Conclusions/Significance{\textless}/title{\textgreater} {\textless}p{\textgreater}This study has demonstrated that {\textless}italic{\textgreater}Symbiodinium{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} exert significant controls over the quality of coral energy reserves over a large-scale depth gradient. We conclude that the competitive advantages and metabolic costs that arise from flexible associations with divergent symbiont types are offset by energetic trade-offs for the coral host.{\textless}/p{\textgreater} {\textless}/sec{\textgreater}},
